## Worker Parallel Mode

{% if worker_worktree_parallel_enabled %}
Opt-in worktree task parallelism is enabled by `identity.worker_parallel_mode={{ worker_parallel_mode }}`. Use it only after `@lead` or the operator has posted live ACP `cwd` smoke-test evidence for this board.

The `worker-parallel-scheduler` skill is the authoritative source for:
- Cap-aware scheduler (4 active concurrent, one-per-tick spawn rate)
- Atomic spawn gate (`/tmp/mc-wt-scheduler-${BOARD_ID}-${AGENT_ID}.lock`)
- Deterministic board-scoped worktree paths (`/tmp/mc-$BOARD_SHORT-wt-$TASK_SHORT`)
- Per-board merge-back lock (`/tmp/mc-wt-merge-${BOARD_ID}.lock`, 60s flock)
- Worktree pre-merge review before merge-back
- ACP spawn payload integration (`acp-delegation` § Worktree Task Mode)

Cap = 4 active implementation tasks unless operator raises it. "Active" = `ACP_EXECUTOR_STARTED` marker + no processed child completion. Parked, blocked, or `operator_decision_required=true` tasks do NOT count. Cap is concurrent-max, not per-tick budget — ramp-up takes 4 cycles from 0→4.

On any worktree create, merge, cleanup, or ACP `cwd` uncertainty: stop parallelism, post one structured blocker with exact failing command/output, continue in sequential main-workspace mode until lead/operator re-enables.
{% else %}
Default to one active implementation task. Do not create git worktrees,
isolated sessions, or parallel workspace branches during heartbeat work.
Those isolation paths have previously hidden state and caused stale merges.

When multiple assigned tasks are present, continue the oldest active
`in_progress` task first. If none is active, pick one eligible task and finish
it through evidence, ACP post-review, and handoff before starting another.

Only if `@lead` explicitly routes independent parallel slices may you run more
than one ACP child. In that case, use `acp-delegation` with disjoint file/AC
ownership, unique labels, and parent-owned final integration. Do not move
status or post completion evidence from child output until `acp-post-review`
passes.
{% endif %}
{% endif %}
{% endif %}
